        'name': 'ISO 23247 – Digital Twin Framework for Manufacturing',
        'description': 'Published in 2021, this standard defines a development framework for Digital Twins in manufacturing, organized into four parts: Overview and General Principles, Reference Architecture, Digital Representation of Physical Manufacturing Elements, and Information Exchange. Part 2 (Reference Architecture) is particularly relevant, detailing an entity-based architecture with four key entities: Observable Manufacturing Element (OME), Data Collection and Device Control Entity, Digital Twin Entity, and User Entity. Each entity comprises Functional Entities (FEs) for specific tasks (e.g., data transformation, user interfacing). The standard provides a structured approach to defining roles and interactions but does not specify implementation details for FEs (e.g., OPC UA mentioned as a potential implementation choice).',
